Description
===========
envtag is a simple audio tagger using taglib's c bindings. Interaction is done
using environment variables which makes it perfect for shell scripts.

Examples
========
* Reading tag information:
eval `envtag /path/to/audio/file`
echo "Title: $TITLE"
echo "Artist: $ARTIST"
echo "Album: $ALBUM"
echo "Comment: $COMMENT"
echo "Genre: $GENRE"
echo "Year: $YEAR"
echo "Track: $TRACK"

* Saving tag information:
COMMENT="Tagged by envtag" envtag -s *.mp3

* Changing file format preserving tag information
eval `envtag -E /path/to/audio/file` # exports tag information
decoder /path/to/audio/file | encoder /path/to/audio/file.new
envtag -s /path/to/audio/file.new # grabs exported tag information and saves it

* Run script, see examples/lua for example scripts
envtag -S /path/to/script.lua /path/to/audio/file
